news.title: Goa: Builders seek till December 31 for accounts submission
news.para: Goa Chamber of Commerce and Industry (GCCI) has written to Goa RERA on behalf of local builders and real estate developers about the challenges posed by the pandemic and the limited resources available to small builders.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC shrinks scheme to pay developers with credit notes
news.para: The proposal for constructing 4,000 PAP units by way of credit notes and Transfer of Development Rights (TDR) has been placed before the BMC’s improvements committee for approval.

news.title: No room for graft as building approvals in Chennai get smoother
news.para: Making the process completely online, the civic body has now made it mandatory for all online documents to have the name and mobile number of the property owner.

news.title: Walton Street BlackSoil invests Rs 110 crore in Hyderabad & Chennai housing projects
news.para: In Q2 2021, more than half of the new housing projects launched across India were in the affordable and mid-income residential segment.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses interim relief to Yes Bank in a case against Asit Koticha, ASK Group
news.para: The genesis of the dispute lies in the credit facility of Rs 330 crore extended by Yes Bank in 2015 to Lily Realty Pvt Ltd, a company owned by Asit Koticha. At the time of securing the loan facility, Koticha had extended ‘Shortfall Security’ under which if the realty firm fails to pay its dues to the Yes Bank, he will pay the shortfall.

news.title: Birla Corporation plans to double cement capacity to 30 million tons in five years
news.para: "Plans are afoot to reach a target of 30 MTPA by 2027," Lodha told shareholders. This is a new target set for the company which had earlier said it would raise its production capacity to 25 MTPA by 2025, the statement said.

news.title: India likely to receive cross-border realty investment of $2.5 billion in 2022: Knight Frank
news.para: The US, UK, Germany, France and the Netherlands are forecast to be the top destinations for cross border real estate investment in 2022.

news.title: Allahabad HC directs state govt to reply on leasehold to freehold conversion in Noida
news.para: According to Jain, the government lawyer informed the court that the appeal by residents was under active consideration and sought more time since the policy decision required a cabinet approval.

news.title: China Evergrande to sell $1.5 billion stake in Shengjing Bank to state firm
news.para: Shengjing Bank, one of the main lenders to Evergrande, had demanded that all net proceeds from the disposal be used to settle the financial liabilities of the property developer due to the lender, Evergrande said in an exchange filing.

news.title: Delhi: SDMC to roll back hiked property tax rates for commercial rented properties
news.para: According to officials, the tax on rented commercial properties was increased on the recommendations of the Municipal Valuation Committee-3 (MVC-3) which was implemented in April last year.

news.title: HeidelbergCement buys 45% stake in US-based Command Alkon
news.para: Thoma Bravo, one of the largest software-focused private equity firms, will keep a 55% in the company, which HeidelbergCement said has the biggest installed software base in the global construction materials sector.

news.title: UK office landlords may not see immediate threat from hybrid work: Citigroup
news.para: The brokerage firm raised its ratings on Land Securities and British Land to "neutral" from "sell" while arguing that the ongoing shift to hybrid work models could take a while.

news.title: UK mortgage lending resumes after tax break blip, consumers cautious
news.para: Net mortgage lending increased by 5.293 billion pounds ($7.24 billion) in August, bouncing back from July's net repayment of 1.758 billion pounds. New mortgage approvals fell slightly to 74,453.

news.title: HC issues notice to Andhra Pradesh government over new property tax system
news.para: The tax payers’ association moved the high court challenging the new property tax regime in which tax is levied based on the capital value of the property instead of annual rental income.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to conduct another survey of buildings' condition
news.para: BBMP Chief Commissioner Gaurav Gupta said," I have asked them to take up another survey on the condition of buildings in the city. A team led by joint commissioners will take up the survey at the zonal levels. Currently, the focus will be on the south zone where I have asked the officials to complete a fresh survey within 30 days.”
